text: Kadyrgulovo () is a rural locality (a village) and the administrative center of Kadyrgulovsky Selsoviet, Davlekanovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 234 as of 2010. == Geography == It is located on the Urshak River. == References == Category:Rural localities in Davlekanovsky District
title: Kadyrgulovo
